  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n`curl` (`192.168.1.10`) unable to get response from `Teku` beacon node (`192.168.1.100`) which was started with `--rest-api-host-allowlist=192.168.1.10, 127.0.0.1, localhost`.\r\n\r\nBut \r\n\r\n`curl` (`192.168.1.10`) was able to receive response from `Teku` beacon node (`192.168.1.100`) which was started with `--rest-api-host-allowlist=192.168.1.100, 127.0.0.1, localhost`.\r\n\r\nI think filter which sits inside `Teku` beacon node incorrectly compares local address with `allow-list` instead of comparing remote address.\r\n\r\n### Versions\r\n* Software version:\r\n```\r\nteku/v23.9.0/linux-x86_64/-na-openjdk64bitservervm-java-17\r\n```\r\n* Java version:\r\n```\r\nopenjdk 17.0.8.1 2023-08-24\r\nOpenJDK Runtime Environment (build 17.0.8.1+1)\r\nOpenJDK 64-Bit Server VM (build 17.0.8.1+1, mixed mode)\r\n```\r\n* OS Name & Version:\r\n```\r\nArchLinux\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
